summary: Big Hit Entertainment thanks fans for #IDOLCHALLENGE!
title: Big Hit Entertainment thanks fans for #IDOLCHALLENGE!
excerpt: Big Hit Entertainment is thanking ARMYs all around for starting the #IDOLCHALLENGE that has been taking the web by storm. According to Big Hit Entertainment, the #IDOLCHALLENGE may have started when South African ARMYs began doing the challenge and then spreading globally. Due to the major success, Big Hit decided to create a video of some of the participants. However, in order to do so, Big Hit must have individuals consent so make sure to send Big Hit your consent.

summary: BTS to focus solely on their world tour 'Love Yourself' in Los Angeles; will not be taking part in any interviews
title: BTS to focus solely on their world tour 'Love Yourself' in Los Angeles; will not be taking part in any interviews
excerpt: On August 30th, It was announced that BTS will not be holding any interviews during their stay in Los Angeles for their world tour 'Love Yourself'. ABC7 Entertainment Reporter, George Pennacchio, shared on Twitter how BTS will not be taking part in any interviews in order to focus on their concerts: "Okay #BTSARMY, I hate to break this news but I learned today that BTS has now decided to turn down ALL interview requests while they're in LA. I'm told the guys want to focus on their shows 'and are doing absolutely nothing else'. I'll still cover the concert for you. #BTS"

caption: HAPPY BIRTHDAY JEON JUNGKOOK!!! Our muscular bunny is 22/21 years old today (Well in Korea, where I am it’s tmr). I used to think he was the cool one in the group that can do anything, and is really chic. But turns out he is not like that. He is the cutest, and very shy. He also loves his hyungs so much, and cares about them like their his family. He, and all of Bangtan, inspire me to be the best of myself and love myself. Happy Birthday little bunny. You are my Euphoria, and ARMYs love you. 😍😍
